pronunciation: nyinganyinga, kurakura, ryama, ryama komeho, humburuka, nyonga(o)
definitions: FORWARD; FURTHER FORWARD; ON (e.g., THE CATTLE MOVED ON/Ozongombe za humburura); SLOWLY
Example: WHAT IS YOUR NAME?/Ena roye oove ani?
General term for nausea. Specifically: NAUSEA CAUSED BY TO MUCH FOOD/ongi.
Example: I NEARLY WENT/Mba hara okuyenda.
General term for need. Specifically: FOOD/oungorovi.
Example: THE MAN IS NEGATIVE, HE DOES NOT WANT TO HELP ME/Omundu ma sisivara ke nokuvanga okundjivatera.
Example: THE OLD MAN IS SITTING NEXT TO THE HOUSE/Omukururume wa haama mene yondjuwo.
Used for PEOPLE/Ovandu muvyu. Used for BEASTS/Ozongombe muvyu.
General term for no; also used as NO, NOT AT ALL/Ayee kako.
MAKE A; MAKE A (TO DISTURB SOMEONE); MAKE A.
